{
  "stem": "8892.5",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My mother's cousin in New York who lived in Long Island waited for us with a big bouquet, and when we arrived-- See, I have to tell you first, that when we were in Sweden, that nine months, every single week, or at least every second week, I would get from one cousin $20, $25 from the other one, and [INAUDIBLE] whatever.",
      "word_count": 62
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my uncle and aunt were older.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My uncle, when I came out, had his first heart attack, and he just made-- he worked for his brother.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But his brothers were a big, large family who's no relation to me, just know.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They just took us into the center of their life.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They're the one who send the money for the ticket, which was $300 those days-- it was a lot of money-- for each of us, and then every week.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So what we did, the minute we had this [INAUDIBLE] of money, we were already rich.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We bought clothes for ourself in a regular store, and my cousin would, you know, sew.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then first thing, with the first $20, we went-- end of the town was a little bit of a, like a little coffee shop and a restaurant, because this was like a summer place, like any summer-- a small place.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we went, with that first $20 to the bank and cashed it, and bought a big salami, a whole whatchamacallit, you know, a whole piece, a big piece of salami, and their Swedish bread, which happened to be very tasty, but their food was always sweet.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And on the way walking back to our bungalow, we just chunked it and ate it like pigs.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we actually were fed good, and then we started to buy clothes.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
